{
  "stem": "7458.2",
  "chunk_idx": 10,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 38,
      "text": "The Jews had to supply him with anything and everything he wanted, fresh coffee every day.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 39,
      "text": "How they got, it didn't matter.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 40,
      "text": "If you don't get it, I line up a dozen people and shoot them.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 41,
      "text": "The demands were terrible.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 42,
      "text": "The looting-- the Polish neighbors took everything practically they could from us.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 43,
      "text": "And this went on day after day, week after week, between 19-- Ju-- June of 1941 and January of 1943.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 44,
      "text": "By the end of '42, we began to hear some horrible rumors about whole towns and cities being liquidated and taken away to gas-- to concentration camps.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Believe it or not, the Israelis dropped some agents in Poland.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] my sister, Feitche-- and I'll talk about her more later-- who kept a diary, describes an agent who came to Jasionowka and told the Judenrat-- every town, they set up a Judenrat, a group of responsible Jews on whom the Germans could make demands.",
      "word_count": 49
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "It so happens that my cousin, and eventually my brother-in-law, [?",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Schlamisch ?], who's the-- was the head of the Judenrat.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And this Israeli agent, a partisan who came-- who was dropped into Poland, told us about-- he told the Judenrat about what's happening, that Jews are being liquidated by the hundreds of thousands in concentration camps.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Some of them going to labor camps, and others go into a gas chambers, where they are being gassed and burned in crematorium.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Thus, we knew that there was very little hope.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "On the other hand-- that was the bad news.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "The good news was that, by the end of '42, we began to hear that-- we began to hear that things were not going so well on the fronts for the Germans.",
      "word_count": 32
    }
  ],
